message.content: He rose from his breakfast-nook bench and came into the livingroom, where Heather and Merve stood gaping in silence. He came, almost falling forward in an ungainly shuffle, neck bent oddly, arms dangling loosely. Then, abruptly, he drew himself up and walked on the very tips of his toes. He jerked his arms out from his head and yawned agape, drawing in great breaths that became great rafts of ecstasy.
